title: For Sale:  TRAPDOOR CARBINE MODEL 1877
postcontent: This is an 1877 Trapdoor Springfield Carbine, (not a cut down rifle)  in 45-70, used by the US Cavalry during the Indian War Period. It's serial number range places it's manufacture in 1877. This explains some of the up grades found on it. The Buffington Rear sight was added probably near the 1884 period. This carbine sight is correctly marked with the "C" on it's ladder. The front barrel band also has the small indent to accommodate the folded sight. There is a possibility this carbine found it's way from the Indian Wars into the Spanish- American War as well? The bore is bright, the wood is good and the action tight. The metal is bright with most of the patina gone. It is in very good condition for it's age of almost 140 years. Will ship as no FFL required.
